value.0: Alexei Bratovich Strauss is an elder of clan Ventrue and the regional Prince of the Kindred of New York, installed by the Camarilla Elders nearly a century ago. Prince Strauss, together with his childe Marissa Werner and loyal Brujah Sheriff Joshua Erwin, campaigned for complete Camarilla control of the city, successfully pushing the Anarchist movement out of New York in 1926. The Sabbat was later defeated in 1940, a war which brought former Sheriff Erwin his True Death. Strauss later chose the macabre Nosferatu leatherface known only as 'Julius' as his Sheriff, an act which both affronted and appauled the majority of the Camarilla Elders. Despite this political setback, the Prince and his Sheriff drove off the Inquisition of 1991, keeping the casualties of both Kindred and Kine to a minimum. Prince Strauss has since ruled a relatively peaceful kingdom in New York, as neither the Anarchs, Sabbat, or Inquisitors have returned in great numbers. Alexei is considered something of a local legend and hero amongst local Camarilla Kindred, as his peerless grasp of tactics and decisive management abilities have kept New York safe and relatively casualty-free, even in the face of incurring war.

Prince Strauss' current Sheriff, known only as 'Julius' to the other Kindred, is a Leatherface Nosferatu. Diagnosed as clinically psychotic and incapable of rational thought or action, the Camarilla Elders had originally deemed Julius a walking Masquerade violation and an Inquisition waiting to happen. Ironically, Prince Strauss later employed the Nosferatu when the Inquisition arrived for other reasons, and with his assistance was able to drive them off with little in the way of casualties. Curiously, Julius' demeanour upon joining with Prince Strauss became reserved, docile, and loyal. Never acting out of turn, the deathly silent killer now serves as the Prince's right hand Executioner, bringing the unruly or chaotic to 'justice' at the Prince's command.
Made of durable leather straps and padding, this vest provides moderate protection against the harmful effects combat has on the human body. It can be worn either over or under clothing.
